## Spec-Driven Development

This project uses Spec-Driven Development (SDD). Specs live in `.specs/specs/{feature-name}/` with three files: `requirements.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`.

- Before implementing any non-trivial feature, create a spec first
- Always read `.specs/steering/*.md` before generating specs or making architectural decisions
- Full SDD rules and workflow: read `sdd/RULES.md` when doing any spec work
- Specs use EARS notation: `WHEN [trigger] THE SYSTEM SHALL [behavior]`
- Three phases with mandatory approval gates: Requirements → Design → Tasks
- Never auto-advance phases — wait for explicit user approval (e.g., "LGTM")
- For bugfix specs, always include an "Unchanged Behavior" section to prevent regressions
